      "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
      "body": "Some comments or thoughts:\r\n1) It is awesome to see that the instructions are simple - fork the repo and rename it as .github public repo. If a customer does this it will add >20 templates to their repo - will spoil their experience. Any thoughts? Keep only P0 templates or organize with resource/language pivot so they can delete the directories that are not needed.\r\n2) If you have folder structure and an organization copies it, does it show all templates in flat structure or organize them? If it is organizing in folders it probably helps solving #1 and makes it easier as well.\r\n3) Should we be calling this as azure\\action-workflow-templates  as these are templates than samples.\r\n\r\nAssuming this work is in progress, few more to be fixed: \r\n- Guidelines to select/author links needs to be fixed (follow it based on closure on #1)\r\n- No sample of application code at all in any of these repos, https://github.com/Azure/actions-workflow-samples/tree/workflow-templates/workflow-templates/AppService\r\n- Every template should have comments included so customers know what to change and modify.\r\n",
